values:
Alright, so a local band called Stallions Versus Unicorns plays this amazing song called Ruby Park. It was a rainy day and the mood was fitting enough for Jenna and I to come up with the idea to storyboard a music video for it...
Time stops, He caught a glimpse of her face. Red is hanging out with her friends, Boy walks by. They spin at such a tranquil pace. Red looks at Boy, they lock eyes for a moment. She moves in such delicate ways. The break eye contact and Red walks on without her friends. They run down the boardwalk. Boy runs past Red. He laughs, slowing to a stop- Boy stops, smiles a little and turns to Red who glances at him but looks away. ..and finally he finds the nerve to talk. Boy turns and walks back to Red. I'M STUCK IN SLOW MOTION THE WORLD IS RESTLESS Boy talks to Red, she laughs a little THIS HOLLYWOOD MOMENT, The two stare at each other. THIS NIGHT IS ENDLESS Red laughs a little and glances down. AND IN THAT RED DRESS, SHE IS BEAUTIFUL. Boy takes her chin and they smile at each other. Soft breeze from the Oceanside. They run on the beach, holding hands. Stars hang, bringing softer light. They trip and fall. Red lays down, Boy just looks at her. She smiles, as he holds her tight. Red sits up and Boy wraps his arms around her. I'M STUCK IN SLOW MOTION They slowly start to kiss and everyone is moving faster then them. THE WORLD IS RESTLESS Another girls walks up and interrupts. THIS HOLLYWOOD MOMENT, Red pushes Boy off and walks off. THIS NIGHT IS ENDLESS Girls stands there and Boy tries to get up and follow Red. AND IN THAT RED DRESS, SHE IS BEAUTIFUL. Red runs off, slows to a walk. [Sleeping in Ruby Park, Far out shot of Boy curling up- pulling his knees close to him. and somehow it feels so real. Boy puts his head on his knees. I wake, I've lost my mind- Boy sits up and leans head against bars. So sleeping, I'll slip away... Boy closes eyes. to Ruby Park Flashback of Red and Boy on equipment. To Ruby Park.] The memory fades. I'M STUCK IN SLOW MOTION Red and Boy are swinging. THE WORLD IS RESTLESS Red laying on a table staring at the sky, Boy is just watching her. THIS HOLLYWOOD MOMENT, THIS NIGHT IS ENDLESS Red walks down a slide and Boy follows and hugs her. AND IN THAT RED DRESS, Flashback to the boardwalk, they pull away from the kiss. SHE IS BEAUTIFUL. Red smiles and bites her lip. She did some crazy things Red yells at Boy And he said some pretty stupid lines Boy yells back. But finally they were lost for words Red and Boy stare at each other, and Red wipes her eyes though she is not crying much. They were lost for words. Zoom/out with shots- the two on the bridge, Red turns and walks away It's in some need of reconstruction to make it more interesting and fit the song a little better, so this is only version one. Any thoughts would be nice... We'd film most of it at Gray's Lake, I think. If you're not cool enough to know who SVU is, go here. The song is Ruby Park- we're not using the acoustic version for the video...

You know what's creepy?

Creepy people.
Dear Yellowcard: Please quit making a mockery of music.

So, I'm starting this journal up... but don't expect too much. Most of it will probably fail to make sense and I'm sure it will all lack substance. 

I didn't want to annoy people on my real journal's friends list, and this was my solution. Sometimes you just have random shit to write, and no reason not to.

Short story even shorter: this journal=random thoughts.
